MIDLAND COGENERATION VENTURE LIMITED PARTNERSHIP FERC ELECTRIC RATE SCHEDULE NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Midland Cogeneration Venture Limited Partnership ("MCV") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a facility located in Midland, Michigan ("Facility") to the Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator, Inc. ("Midwest ISO"). This rate schedule sets forth MCV's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the Facility pursuant to the Midwest ISO Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff ("Midwest ISO Tariff"). Payments from the Midwest ISO shall be in accordance with Schedule 2 of the Midwest ISO Tariff under which MCV receives compensation as accepted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
MCV's revenue requirement is set forth below.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Fixed Capability Component: Annual Revenue Requirement is $6,000,000.
Fixed Capability Component: Monthly Revenue Requirement is $500,000.
